    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-03-31T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-03-31T03:00:00-05:00" n="271"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d271">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6124: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-31T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 31, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 31—7:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>296. My 293, March 30, 4 p.m.<note n="84" xml:id="d271fn84">Not printed.</note>
                    Japanese Legation informs me that Japanese Ambassador to Manchukuo had replied
                    to Japanese Legation’s report to him of my note of March 28 stating that matter
                    has been referred to the appropriate authorities and that more specific reply
                    must await report of investigation. In answer to this Legation’s inquiry as to
                    action taken to prevent recurrence of bombing imperilling Americans and property
                    at Taitowying Japanese Legation stated that all interested parties had been
                    advised of my report of March 28. On March 23 Lockhart reported that Japanese
                    Consul at Tientsin had stated that he had reported matter to appropriate
                    military authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
